<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-01-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-01-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="638" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Pearson</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-06"><hi rend="italic">January 6,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Loomis instructs Mr. Pearson to forward the Labaree indemnity to the
                            Department, and informs him that the President cordially commends his
                            energetic and efficient action in this case.)</p>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>